'''SciDB''' <ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.scidb.org/ | title=SciDB website}}</ref> is an array database designed for multidimensional data management and analytics common to scientific, geospatial, financial, and industrial applications. It is developed by Paradigm4, co-founded by [[Michael Stonebraker]].
== History and Characteristics == [[Michael Stonebraker]] co-created SciDB where, he claims, arrays are 100 or so times faster than a RDBMS on this class of problem.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.theregister.co.uk/2010/09/13/michael_stonebraker_interview | title=Stonebraker interview}}</ref> It is swapping rows and columns for mathematical arrays that put fewer restrictions on the data and can work in any number of dimensions unlike the conventionally widely used [[relational database management system]] model.
